33// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40#elif USING_V8_SHARED
41# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42#else
43# define V8_EXPORT
44#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45
46#else // V8_OS_WIN
47
48// Setup for Linux shared library export.
49#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52# else
53# define V8_EXPORT
54# endif
55#else
56# define V8_EXPORT
57#endif
58
59#endif // V8_OS_WIN

159#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
160 while (false) { \
161 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
162 }
163
195template <class T>
196class Local {
197 public:
198 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
199 template <class S>
200 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
201 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
207 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
208 }
209
213 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
214
218 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
219
220 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
221
222 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
223
230 template <class S>
231 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
232 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
233 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
234 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
235 if (b == 0) return false;
236 return *a == *b;
237 }
238
239 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
240 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
241 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
242 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
243 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
244 if (b == 0) return false;
245 return *a == *b;
246 }
247
254 template <class S>
255 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
256 return !operator==(that);
257 }
258
259 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
260 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
261 return !operator==(that);
262 }
263
269 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
270#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
271 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
272 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
273 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
274#endif
275 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
276 }
277
283 template <class S>
284 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
285 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
286 }
287
293 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
294 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
295 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
296
297 private:
298 friend class Utils;
299 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
300 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
301 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
302 template<class F> friend class Local;
303 template <class F>
304 friend class MaybeLocal;
305 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
306 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
307 friend class String;
308 friend class Object;
309 friend class Context;
310 friend class Private;
311 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
312 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
313 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
314 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
315 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
316 friend class HandleScope;
317 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
318 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
319 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
320 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
321 template <class F>
322 friend class ReturnValue;
323
324 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
325 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
326 T* val_;
327};

347template <class T>
348class MaybeLocal {
349 public:
350 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
351 template <class S>
352 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
353 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
354 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
355 }
356
357 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
358
363 template <class S>
364 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
365 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
366 return !IsEmpty();
367 }
368
373 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
374
379 template <class S>
380 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
381 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
382 }
383
384 private:
385 T* val_;
386};

409static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
410static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
411
412template <typename T>
413class WeakCallbackInfo {
414 public:
415 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
416
417 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
418 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
419 Callback* callback)
420 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
421 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
422 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
423 }
424 }
425
426 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
427 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
428 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
429
430 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
431 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
432 return embedder_fields_[0];
433 }
434 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
435 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
436 return embedder_fields_[1];
437 }
438
439 V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
440 bool IsFirstPass() const) {
441 return callback_ != nullptr;
442 }
443
444 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451
452 private:
453 Isolate* isolate_;
454 T* parameter_;
455 Callback* callback_;
456 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
457};
458
459
460// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
461// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
462// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
463// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
464// possible to request a second pass callback.
465enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
466
480template <class T> class PersistentBase {
481 public:
486 V8_INLINE void Reset();
491 template <class S>
492 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
493
498 template <class S>
499 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
500
501 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
502 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
503
504 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
505 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
506 }
507
508 template <class S>
509 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
510 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
511 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
512 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
513 if (b == NULL) return false;
514 return *a == *b;
515 }
516
517 template <class S>
518 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
519 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
520 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
521 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
522 if (b == NULL) return false;
523 return *a == *b;
524 }
525
526 template <class S>
527 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
528 return !operator==(that);
529 }
530
531 template <class S>
532 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
533 return !operator==(that);
534 }
535
543 template <typename P>
544 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
545 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
546 WeakCallbackType type);
547
555 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
556
557 template<typename P>
558 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
559
560 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
561 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
562
568 V8_INLINE void RegisterExternalReference(Isolate* isolate) const;
569
576 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
577
583 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();
584
585 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
586
588 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
589
591 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
592
597 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
598
603 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
604
605 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
606 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
607
608 private:
609 friend class Isolate;
610 friend class Utils;
611 template<class F> friend class Local;
612 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
613 template <class F>
614 friend class Global;
615 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
616 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
617 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
618 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
619 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
620 friend class Object;
621
622 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
623 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
624
625 T* val_;
626};

676template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
677 public:
681 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
687 template <class S>
688 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
689 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
690 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
691 }
697 template <class S, class M2>
698 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
699 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
700 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
701 }
708 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
709 Copy(that);
710 }
711 template <class S, class M2>
712 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
713 Copy(that);
714 }
715 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
716 Copy(that);
717 return *this;
718 }
719 template <class S, class M2>
720 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
721 Copy(that);
722 return *this;
723 }
729 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
730 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
731 }
732
733 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
734 template <class S>
735 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
736#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
737 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
738 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
739 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
740#endif
741 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
742 }
743
744 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
745 template <class S>
746 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
747 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
748 }
749
750 private:
751 friend class Isolate;
752 friend class Utils;
753 template<class F> friend class Local;
754 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
755 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
756
757 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
758 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
759 template<class S, class M2>
760 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
761};

769template <class T>
770class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
771 public:
775 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
781 template <class S>
782 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
783 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
784 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
785 }
791 template <class S>
792 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
793 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
794 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
795 }
799 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
800 other.val_ = nullptr;
801 }
802 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
806 template <class S>
807 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
808 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
809 if (this != &rhs) {
810 this->Reset();
811 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
812 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
813 }
814 return *this;
815 }
819 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
820
821 /*
822 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
823 */
824 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
825
826 Global(const Global&) = delete;
827 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
828
829 private:
830 template <class F>
831 friend class ReturnValue;
832 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
833};

969class ScriptOriginOptions {
970 public:
971 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
972 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
973 bool is_module = false)
974 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
975 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
976 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
977 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
978 : flags_(flags &
979 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
980
981 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
982 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
983 }
984 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
985 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
986 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
987
988 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
989
990 private:
991 enum {
992 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
993 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
994 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
995 kIsModule = 1 << 3
996 };
997 const int flags_;
998};

1039class V8_EXPORT UnboundScript {
1040 public:
1044 Local<Script> BindToCurrentContext();

1173class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1174 public:
1182 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1183 enum BufferPolicy {
1184 BufferNotOwned,
1185 BufferOwned
1186 };
1187
1188 CachedData()
1189 : data(NULL),
1190 length(0),
1191 rejected(false),
1192 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1193
1194 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1195 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1196 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1197 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1198 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1199 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1200 ~CachedData();
1201 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1202 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1203 const uint8_t* data;
1204 int length;
1205 bool rejected;
1206 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1207
1208 // Prevent copying.
1209 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1210 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1211 };
1212
1216 class Source {
1217 public:
1218 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1219 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1220 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1221 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1222 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1223 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1224
1225 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1226 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1227 // alive.
1228 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1229
1230 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1231
1232 // Prevent copying.
1233 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1234 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1235
1236 private:
1237 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1238
1239 Local<String> source_string;
1240
1241 // Origin information
1242 Local<Value> resource_name;
1243 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1244 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1245 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1246 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1247
1248 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1249 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1250 // set when calling a compile method.
1251 CachedData* cached_data;
1252 };

3033 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3034 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3035 //
3036 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3037 //
3038 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3039 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3040 //
3041 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.

3050 // Note that if the object has an interceptor the property will be set
3051 // locally, but since the interceptor takes precedence the local property
3052 // will only be returned if the interceptor doesn't return a value.
3053 //
3054 // Note also that this only works for named properties.

3542template<typename T>
3543class ReturnValue {
3544 public:
3545 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3546 : value_(that.value_) {
3547 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3548 }
3549 // Local setters
3550 template <typename S>
3551 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3552 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3553 template <typename S>
3554 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3555 template <typename S>
3556 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3557 // Fast primitive setters
3558 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3559 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3560 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3561 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3562 // Fast JS primitive setters
3563 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3564 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3565 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3566 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3567 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3568
3569 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3570 template <typename S>
3571 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3572
3573 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3574 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3575 // value.
3576 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3577
3578 private:
3579 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3580 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3581 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3582 template <class F, class G, class H>
3583 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3584 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3585 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3586 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3587 internal::Object** value_;
3588};

4054// TODO(mtrofin): rename WasmCompiledModule to WasmModuleObject, for
4055// consistency with internal APIs.
4056class V8_EXPORT WasmCompiledModule : public Object {
4057 public:
4058 typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> SerializedModule;
4059 // A buffer that is owned by the caller.
4060 typedef std::pair<const uint8_t*, size_t> CallerOwnedBuffer;
4061
4062 // An opaque, native heap object for transferring wasm modules. It
4063 // supports move semantics, and does not support copy semantics.
4064 class TransferrableModule final {
4065 public:
4066 TransferrableModule(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4067 TransferrableModule(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4068
4069 TransferrableModule& operator=(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4070 TransferrableModule& operator=(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4071
4072 private:
4073 typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> OwnedBuffer;
4074 friend class WasmCompiledModule;
4075 TransferrableModule(OwnedBuffer&& code, OwnedBuffer&& bytes)
4076 : compiled_code(std::move(code)), wire_bytes(std::move(bytes)) {}
4077
4078 OwnedBuffer compiled_code = {nullptr, 0};
4079 OwnedBuffer wire_bytes = {nullptr, 0};
4080 };
4081
4082 // Get an in-memory, non-persistable, and context-independent (meaning,
4083 // suitable for transfer to another Isolate and Context) representation
4084 // of this wasm compiled module.
4085 TransferrableModule GetTransferrableModule();
4086
4087 // Efficiently re-create a WasmCompiledModule, without recompiling, from
4088 // a TransferrableModule.
4089 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> FromTransferrableModule(
4090 Isolate* isolate, const TransferrableModule&);
4091
4092 // Get the wasm-encoded bytes that were used to compile this module.
4093 Local<String> GetWasmWireBytes();
4094
4095 // Serialize the compiled module. The serialized data does not include the
4096 // uncompiled bytes.
4097 SerializedModule Serialize();
4098
4099 // If possible, deserialize the module, otherwise compile it from the provided
4100 // uncompiled bytes.
4101 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> DeserializeOrCompile(
4102 Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4103 const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4104 V8_INLINE static WasmCompiledModule* Cast(Value* obj);
4105
4106 private:
4107 // TODO(ahaas): please remove the friend once streamed compilation is
4108 // implemented
4109 friend class WasmModuleObjectBuilder;
4110
4111 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Deserialize(
4112 Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4113 const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4114 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Compile(Isolate* isolate,
4115 const uint8_t* start,
4116 size_t length);
4117 static CallerOwnedBuffer AsCallerOwned(
4118 const TransferrableModule::OwnedBuffer& buff) {
4119 return {buff.first.get(), buff.second};
4120 }
4121
4122 WasmCompiledModule();
4123 static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
4124};

6359struct JitCodeEvent {
6360 enum EventType {
6361 CODE_ADDED,
6362 CODE_MOVED,
6363 CODE_REMOVED,
6364 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6365 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6366 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6367 };
6368 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6369 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6370 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6371 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6372 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6373 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6374
6375 // Type of event.
6376 EventType type;
6377 // Start of the instructions.
6378 void* code_start;
6379 // Size of the instructions.
6380 size_t code_len;
6381 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6382 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6383 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6384 // code line information which is returned from the
6385 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6386 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6387 void* user_data;
6388
6389 struct name_t {
6390 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6391 // zero-terminated.
6392 const char* str;
6393 // Number of chars in str.
6394 size_t len;
6395 };
6396
6397 struct line_info_t {
6398 // PC offset
6399 size_t offset;
6400 // Code postion
6401 size_t pos;
6402 // The position type.
6403 PositionType position_type;
6404 };
6405
6406 union {
6407 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6408 struct name_t name;
6409
6410 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6411 struct line_info_t line_info;
6412
6413 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6414 void* new_code_start;
6415 };
6416};
6417
6423enum RAILMode {
6424 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6425 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6426 // Throughput may be throttled.
6427 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6428 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6429 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6430 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6431 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6432 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6433 // in this mode.
6434 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6435 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6436 // turn off latency optimizations.
6437 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6438};
6439
6443enum JitCodeEventOptions {
6444 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
6445 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
6446 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
6447};

8071template <class T>
8072class Maybe {
8073 public:
8074 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8075 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8076
8080 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8081
8086 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8087 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8088 return IsJust();
8089 }
8090
8095 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8096 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8097 return value_;
8098 }
8099
8104 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8105 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8106 }
8107
8108 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8109 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8110 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8111 }
8112
8113 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8114 return !operator==(other);
8115 }
8116
8117 private:
8118 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8119 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8120
8121 bool has_value_;
8122 T value_;
8123
8124 template <class U>
8125 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8126 template <class U>
8127 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8128};
8129
8130
8131template <class T>
8132inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8133 return Maybe<T>();
8134}
8135
8136
8137template <class T>
8138inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8139 return Maybe<T>(t);
8140}

8676namespace internal {
8677
8678const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8679const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8680const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8681
8682// Tag information for HeapObject.
8683const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8684const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8685const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8686
8687// Tag information for Smi.
8688const int kSmiTag = 0;
8689const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8690const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8691
8692template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8693
8694template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8695V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8696 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8697 uintptr_t tagged_value =
8698 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8699 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8700}
8701
8702// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8703template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8704 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8705 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8706 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8707 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8708 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8709 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8710 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8711 }
8712 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8713 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8714 }
8715 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8716 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8717 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8718 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8719 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8720 //
8721 // CAUTION: The original code below:
8722 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8723 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8724 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8725 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8726 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8727 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8728 }
8729};
8730
8731// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8732template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8733 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8734 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8735 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8736 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8737 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8738 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8739 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8740 }
8741 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8742 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8743 }
8744 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8745 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8746 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8747 }
8748};
8749
8750typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
8751const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
8752const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
8753V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
8754V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }
8755
8761class Internals {
8762 public:
8763 // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
8764 // the implementation of v8.
8765 static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
8766 static const int kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset =
8767 1 * kApiPointerSize + kApiIntSize;
8768 static const int kStringResourceOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
8769
8770 static const int kOddballKindOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize + sizeof(double);
8771 static const int kForeignAddressOffset = kApiPointerSize;
8772 static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
8773 static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
8774 static const int kContextHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
8775 static const int kContextEmbedderDataIndex = 5;
8776 static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x0f;
8777 static const int kStringEncodingMask = 0x8;
8778 static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
8779 static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x0a;
8780
8781 static const int kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset = 0 * kApiPointerSize;
8782 static const int kExternalMemoryOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize;
8783 static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
8784 kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
8785 static const int kIsolateRootsOffset = kExternalMemoryLimitOffset +
8786 kApiInt64Size + kApiInt64Size +
8787 kApiPointerSize + kApiPointerSize;
8788 static const int kUndefinedValueRootIndex = 4;
8789 static const int kTheHoleValueRootIndex = 5;
8790 static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 6;
8791 static const int kTrueValueRootIndex = 7;
8792 static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 8;
8793 static const int kEmptyStringRootIndex = 9;
8794
8795 static const int kNodeClassIdOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize;
8796 static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
8797 static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
8798 static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
8799 static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
8800 static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
8801 static const int kNodeIsIndependentShift = 3;
8802 static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;
8803
8804 static const int kJSApiObjectType = 0xbb;
8805 static const int kJSObjectType = 0xbc;
8806 static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
8807 static const int kOddballType = 0x82;
8808 static const int kForeignType = 0x86;
8809
8810 static const int kUndefinedOddballKind = 5;
8811 static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;

8815 V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);

8817#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8818 CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
8819#endif
8820 }
8821
8822 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
8823 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
8824 kHeapObjectTag);
8825 }
8826
8827 V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
8828 return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
8829 }
8830
8831 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8832 return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
8833 }
8834
8835 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8836 return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
8837 }
8838
8839 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
8840 typedef internal::Object O;
8841 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
8842 // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
8843 // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
8844 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
8845 }
8846
8847 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
8848 typedef internal::Object O;
8849 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
8850 }
8851
8852 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
8853 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
8854 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
8855 }
8856
8857 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
8858 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8859 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8860 }
8861
8862 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
8863 bool value, int shift) {
8864 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8865 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8866 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
8867 }
8868
8869 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
8870 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8871 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
8872 }
8873
8874 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
8875 uint8_t value) {
8876 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8877 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
8878 }
8879
8880 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8881 uint32_t slot,
8882 void* data) {
8883 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8884 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8885 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
8886 }
8887
8888 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
8889 uint32_t slot) {
8890 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8891 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8892 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
8893 }
8894
8895 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8896 int index) {
8897 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
8898 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
8899 }
8900
8901 template <typename T>
8902 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
8903 const uint8_t* addr =
8904 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
8905 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
8906 }
8907
8908 template <typename T>
8909 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
8910 typedef internal::Object O;
8911 typedef internal::Internals I;
8912 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
8913 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
8914 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
8915 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
8916 int value_offset =
8917 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8918 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
8919 }
8920};

8936template <class T>
8937Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
8938 if (that == NULL) return Local<T>();
8939 T* that_ptr = that;
8940 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that_ptr);
8941 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
8942 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
8943}

8951 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));

8954template <class T>
8955Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
8956 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
8957 // need to open a handle.
8958 return Local<T>(val_);
8959}

8962template <class T>
8963Local<T> MaybeLocal<T>::ToLocalChecked() {
8964 if (V8_UNLIKELY(val_ == nullptr)) V8::ToLocalEmpty();
8965 return Local<T>(val_);
8966}

8969template <class T>
8970void* WeakCallbackInfo<T>::GetInternalField(int index) const {
8971#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8972 if (index < 0 || index >= kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback) {
8973 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
8974 }
8975#endif
8976 return embedder_fields_[index];
8977}

8980template <class T>
8981T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
8982 if (that == NULL) return NULL;
8983 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that);
8984 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
8985 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
8986 p));
8987}

8990template <class T, class M>
8991template <class S, class M2>
8992void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
8993 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8994 this->Reset();
8995 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
8996 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
8997 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
8998 M::Copy(that, this);
8999}

9002template <class T>
9003bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
9004 typedef internal::Internals I;
9005 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9006 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
9007 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
9008}
9009
9010
9011template <class T>
9012bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
9013 typedef internal::Internals I;
9014 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9015 uint8_t node_state =
9016 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9017 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9018 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9019}
9020
9021
9022template <class T>
9023bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
9024 typedef internal::Internals I;
9025 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9026 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
9027 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
9028}

9031template <class T>
9032void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
9033 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
9034 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9035 val_ = 0;
9036}

9041void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
9042 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9043 Reset();
9044 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
9045 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
9046}

9049template <class T>
9050template <class S>
9051void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate,
9052 const PersistentBase<S>& other) {
9053 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9054 Reset();
9055 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
9056 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
9057}

9108template <class T>
9109void PersistentBase<T>::SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id) {
9110 typedef internal::Internals I;
9111 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
9112 internal::Object** obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
9113 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
9114 *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
9115}

9118template <class T>
9119uint16_t PersistentBase<T>::WrapperClassId() const {
9120 typedef internal::Internals I;
9121 if (this->IsEmpty()) return 0;
9122 internal::Object** obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
9123 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
9124 return *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr);
9125}

9164template<typename T>
9165void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
9166 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
9167 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9168}
9169
9170template<typename T>
9171void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9172 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9173 typedef internal::Internals I;
9174 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9175 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9176 return;
9177 }
9178 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9179}
9180
9181template<typename T>
9182void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9183 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9184 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9185 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9186 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9187 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9188 return;
9189 }
9190 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9191}
9192
9193template<typename T>
9194void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9195 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9196 typedef internal::Internals I;
9197 int root_index;
9198 if (value) {
9199 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9200 } else {
9201 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9202 }
9203 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9204}

9208 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9209 typedef internal::Internals I;
9210 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
9211}

9218}

9229 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
9230 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);

9233template <typename T>
9234Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9235 typedef internal::Internals I;
9236 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9237 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9238 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9239}

9399
9400Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9401#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9402 typedef internal::Object O;
9403 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9404 typedef internal::Internals I;
9405 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9406 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9407 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9408 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9409 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9410 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9411 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9412 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9413 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9414 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9415 }
9416#endif
9417 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9418}
9419
9420
9421void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9422#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9423 typedef internal::Object O;
9424 typedef internal::Internals I;
9425 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9426 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9427 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9428 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9429 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9430 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9431 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9432 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9433 }
9434#endif
9435 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9436}

9454
9455String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9456 typedef internal::Object O;
9457 typedef internal::Internals I;
9458 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9459 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9460 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9461 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9462 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9463 } else {
9464 result = NULL;
9465 }
9466#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9467 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9468#endif
9469 return result;
9470}
9471
9472
9473String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9474 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9475 typedef internal::Object O;
9476 typedef internal::Internals I;
9477 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9478 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9479 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9480 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9481 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9482 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9483 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9484 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9485 }
9486#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9487 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9488#endif
9489 return resource;
9490}

9500
9501bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
9502 typedef internal::Object O;
9503 typedef internal::Internals I;
9504 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9505 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9506 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9507 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
9508}

9513 return FullIsNull();
9514#else
9515 return QuickIsNull();
9516#endif
9517}
9518
9519bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
9520 typedef internal::Object O;
9521 typedef internal::Internals I;
9522 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9523 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9524 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9525 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
9526}

9528bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
9529#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9530 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
9531#else
9532 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
9533#endif
9534}
9535
9536bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
9537 typedef internal::Object O;
9538 typedef internal::Internals I;
9539 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9540 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9541 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9542 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
9543 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
9544}

9555 typedef internal::Object O;
9556 typedef internal::Internals I;
9557 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9558 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9559 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);
9560}

10000int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10001 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10002 typedef internal::Internals I;
10003 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10004 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10005 const int64_t external_memory_limit = *reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10006 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10007 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10008 *external_memory = amount;
10009 if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > external_memory_limit) {
10010 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10011 }
10012 return *external_memory;
10013}

10015Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10016#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10017 typedef internal::Object O;
10018 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
10019 typedef internal::Internals I;
10020 HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
10021 O** result =
10022 HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
10023 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10024#else
10025 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10026#endif
10027}
